@voidspacexyz I can understand your admin issue, but for diagnosing problems we need to be sure it's not just a broken setup that triggers your bug. So far, you just confirm that you are running a prebuilt, upstream Tensorflow.

You really need to get that straight: either use ALL of ours prebuilt binaries (tensorflow, libctc, libdeepspeech), or build everything from compatible source code. Mixing prebuilt binaries would clearly trigger that kind of segfault (I know, I have been there, there might be differences in ABI, in headers, in data structure sizes).

Compatibility with upstream tensorflow cannot be guaranteed, because they don't guarantee C++ API stability. So they might have done some changes to 1.3 API between the snapshot we started worked on, and the release, and the same story can apply to 1.4.

