Still not working for me. No `<meta property="og:image" ...>` in the HTML source codes. However, for now I resolved it by this piece of code that I wrote in `extra_tags.py` under `templatetags` folder. Maybe it will help someone else.

```
@register.simple_tag
def og_image(request):
	path = request.get_full_path()
	domain = request.META['HTTP_HOST']
	default = 'absolute-path-to-your-image'

	img_url = default

	if '/posts/' in path:
		post_slug = path.replace('/posts/', '')

		if len(post_slug) > 0:
			post_slug = post_slug.replace('/', '')

			try:
				post = Post.objects.get(slug=post_slug)
			
				if post.img_url:
					img_url = domain + img_url

			except:
				pass

	return u'<meta property="og:image" content="%s" />' % img_url

```

Then in `base.html` (`<head>...`): `{% og_image request %}`.

