@sellers are you using the flask / connexion swagger generator?
If so then that is because the generated `__main__.py` creates the app within `main()` which called within the  `if __name__ == "__main__"` statement and as such the app will only be created if it's executed directly. WSGI (uwsgi or gunicorn) will instead to load it as a module and not execute the `if` statement.

In this case the solution would simply be to modify that file so the `app` (and `application = app.app`) is created as a variable in the module's namespace (e.g. by moving it outside of `main()`). However, I would keep the `app.run()` command in the `if` =)

