@blampe this is definitely a minor, 1.1.0. We're changing how functionality works in order to provide performance improvements, not fixing existing functionality.

Users should pin to `>= 1, <2` in their `requirements.in`, so that regenerating `requirements.txt` results in the latest 1.x release being installed.

Let's not use patches as a means to ship new functionality, only for fixing existing functionality.

